                " argon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The irradiated uranium sample, a part of a reactor",
                "fuel plate containing approximately 2.5 mg of 235U",
                "and 125 mg of aluminum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "RELFY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The sample was irradiated for 3.85 yr.",
                "The sample was dissolved in the presence of measured",
                "amounts of argon, krypton, and xenon carriers with 6N",
                "hydrochloric acid containing a trace of platinic",
                "chloride as a catalyst. The recovery of each rare gas",
                "was measured; chemical yields were always more than",
                "95%. 42K was allowed to grow in, the argon was removed,",
                " and  then the 42K was counted.  No evidence for 42K",
                "activity  was  observed. An upper limit for 42K",
                "activity was determined by two methods:",
                " (1) the difference between a long count of the sample",
                "and of the background was taken as the number of",
                "atoms of 42K at the beginning of the count, and",
                " (2) a least-squares decay-curve analysis was",
                "performed assuming the presence of 42K and background.",
                "The fission yields obtained from the two methods are",
                " (1.1+-1.7)x10**-11% and (0.6+-0.8)x10**-11%,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
